---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Chickadee Health"
  description="Privacy Policy for Chickadee Health - How we collect, use, and protect your health data."
>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: October 30, 2025</p>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Chickadee Health ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your health information when you use our iOS mobile application and services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Health Data Collection and Use</h2>
          <h3>What We Collect from Apple HealthKit</h3>
          <p>
            Our app collects the following types of health data from Apple HealthKit with your explicit permission:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Heart rate and heart rate variability</li>
            <li>Activity levels and step counts</li>
            <li>Sleep patterns and quality</li>
            <li>Walking speed and mobility metrics</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How We Use Your Health Data</h3>
          <p>
            We analyze your health data to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Detect patterns that may indicate increased fall risk or health concerns</li>
            <li>Send timely alerts to your designated family members when concerning patterns are identified</li>
            <li>Provide you with insights about your health trends within the app</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            <strong>Your health data remains private and is never sold, shared with third parties for marketing purposes, or used for any purpose other than providing our health monitoring service to you.</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>SMS Notifications</h2>
          <h3>How SMS Alerts Work</h3>
          <p>
            When you add family members to your health monitoring network, they will receive SMS text message alerts when our app detects concerning health patterns. These alerts help your loved ones know when to check in with you.
          </p>

          <h3>Phone Number Privacy - Required Disclosure</h3>
          <p class="highlight">
            <strong>Your mobile phone information will not be sold or shared with third parties for promotional or marketing purposes.</strong>
          </p>

          <p>
            We collect and use phone numbers only to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Send health monitoring alerts to designated family members</li>
            <li>Send account and service-related notifications</li>
            <li>Verify user identity during account setup</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            Family members can opt out of SMS alerts at any time by replying STOP to any message. Standard message and data rates may apply based on your mobile carrier's plan.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Data Security and HIPAA Considerations</h2>
          <h3>How We Protect Your Data</h3>
          <p>
            We take data security seriously and implement industry-standard measures to protect your information:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>All health data is encrypted in transit and at rest</li>
            <li>We use secure, authenticated connections for all data transmission</li>
            <li>Access to your data is strictly limited to authorized systems needed to provide our service</li>
            <li>We conduct regular security audits and updates</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>SMS Messages and Protected Health Information (PHI)</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Important:</strong> We do not send Protected Health Information (PHI) via SMS text messages. Our SMS alerts contain only general notifications (such as "concerning health pattern detected") and do not include specific medical data, diagnoses, or detailed health metrics. Detailed information is only available within the secure Chickadee Health app.
          </p>

          <h3>HIPAA Compliance</h3>
          <p>
            Chickadee Health is committed to complying with applicable health data protection regulations. While we handle health information with the highest standards of care, we are not a covered entity under HIPAA. However, we implement HIPAA-aligned security practices to protect your health data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
          <h3>Access and Control</h3>
          <p>
            You have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access your data:</strong> View all health data collected through the app at any time</li>
            <li><strong>Revoke permissions:</strong> Disconnect HealthKit access through your iPhone Settings</li>
            <li><strong>Update family network:</strong> Add or remove family members from SMS alerts</li>
            <li><strong>Opt out of SMS:</strong> You or your family members can stop receiving SMS alerts by replying STOP</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Data Deletion</h3>
          <p>
            You can request deletion of your account and all associated data at any time by:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Using the "Delete Account" option in the app settings, or</li>
            <li>Contacting us at <a href="mailto:privacy@chickadee.family">privacy@chickadee.family</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Upon deletion, we will permanently remove all your health data, account information, and SMS notification preferences within 30 days. Note that some data may be retained for a limited time as required by law or for legitimate business purposes (such as fraud prevention).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
          <p>
            We do not sell your data. We only share your information in the following limited circumstances:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Family members you designate:</strong> General health alerts (not detailed PHI) via SMS</li>
            <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> Trusted partners who help us operate our service (such as cloud hosting and SMS delivery), who are contractually bound to protect your data and use it only for providing services to us</li>
            <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> When required by law, such as in response to valid legal processes</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Chickadee Health is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect health information from children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of significant changes through the app or via email. Your continued use of Chickadee Health after changes become effective constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    background: white;
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-content h1 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal-section h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .legal-section p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    margin-left: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .legal-section li {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-section a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .highlight {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-bg-light);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
  }

  .highlight strong {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  /* Mobile responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    }

    .legal-content h1 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    }

    .legal-section h3 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    }

    .legal-section ul {
      margin-left: var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>
